<br>
Swarm Kiting... well... I know that playing a bard well, and to me that means the ability to twist songs and melee, is very difficult.  A bard that can play 1 song or twist two and melee is not difficult... I have seen bards twist 5 songs and pull before.. now that I feel is a good bard.  So, in order to swarm I would assume, not having played a bard myself I have to assume, would require a player to be excellent in that class.  This is a rare few.  So, let them be.<br>
<br>
The problem I have is this, their ability to kite this many creatures simultaneously.  Our AoE spells, the Al'Kabor line I believe, used to be able to hit a huge number of MoBs.  This was nerfed because &quot;Wizards are too powerful&quot;.  Now they hit a max of 5.  If our, yes I play a wizard, power was too great because we could AoE more than 5 creatures then wouldn't that apply to Bards as well?<br>
<br>
I do not want to see Bards nerfed.. I want the complement wizard spells re-instated.  I want to AoE more than 5 MoBs at a time.  If it is ok for a Bard to kite more than 5 then it should be ok for us.<br>
<br>
Now, my wizard has always been my favorite class.  I have played him for over 3 years now.  I am not, by far, the best Wizard.  I have not dedicated countless hours to the game, I have a job and friends that require an inordinate amount of time (damn RL)  :-)  So, if I have errored a bit in this post be gentle.  I welcome a good debate on these issues.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your time in this matter.  :-)<br>
