Bards are an extremely versatile class but our abilities are fairly weak overall.  Sure, we can swarm-kite for maybe 40 minutes but our mana regen blows.  Pre-PoP we only have a 30% slow, plus it has a dot component and a long recast delay.  To provide effective CC we have to give up one song per mezzed mob and we really can't handle more than 4 although everyone has probably ghetto-mezzed 5 in a pinch.  I can't begin to describe how fucking annoying twisting 4 songs constantly is; those of you who've played a bard above 30 know what I'm talking about.  Bard melee is pure crap, bard AA is arguably the worst in the game, and druids and wizards hate us for swarm-kiting.  Yeah, we have decent manaless dots...with IM3 and a good instrument.  Bard AE songs are even nicer but they still aren't overpowering (have any bards out there with extended notes tried AE kiting?).  Get this through your head: BARDS ARE NOT OVERPOWERED.  Besides, we're all officially disabled thanks to carpal tunnel syndrome :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=haemonculusv3>Haemonculus v3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/29/02 12:12:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> sadf</span><hr size=1> Bards are a secondary support class in most cases. Yes, in some fights they are needed to directly interact with the MoB. Yes, they can output pretty decent DPS with their new chant lineup and a good weapon. No, they are nowhere near Wizards on raids.<br>
