<br>
A lot of bards find this thread interesting. I consider myself a very good swarm kiter. I would like to offer a few observations:<br>
<br>
A good Druid, Wizard, Necro Quadding or pulling 1-3 can certainly stay up with my kill ratio, some I am better than, some are better (kills per hour) than me. <br>
<br>
In terms of that kind of success (in upper levels), outside, and with only certain kinds of mob, that is the only place bards really shine. Their other value is as support to a group (sometimes very valuable--sometimes soso), we can kinda solo singles fear kiting, and do a little better with our 'chant' series of single mob only dots, but we can't approach other classes.<br>
<br>
The days of upper level (45 or so) bards Charm/swarm kiting 20+ groups should be over. The lvl 37 charm that works on up to 52 lvl mobs usually lasts a minute.  Using it with that large a group is a waste of time (mob dies while charmed--no exp, 60 mana, 360 sec regen time, gone). Effective 'swarms' are now in the 3 to 6 range. If you see a bigger one, the bard has probably screwed up and is just trying to pair the number down because he's not getting exp charming, or he is getting very slow exp chanting and at a high risk.<br>
<br>
The bad thing about a bard swarm is, only one mob (the charm) usually has hard aggro on the bard, if a (pick class) runs his quad or fear kite near the bard, all but the charm may aggro on the bypasser.<br>
<br>
Pets of any class have a tendancy to run and aggro swarms, the bard can try and fix this but usually fails and there is a ClusterF that may appear like the bard deliberatly trained someone.<br>
<br>
Not making excuses, but running at full speed, using the pan back view, not everything is easy to see or is as it appears on screen, when swarm kiting, I have pulled my swarm away from a seemingly unknowing runner only to have them 'disappear' and reappear somewhere else. I have also accidentally run someone over. But then, its been done to me by just about every other class (maybe not Clerics and Chanters).<br>
<br>
Bards usually stake an area, seemingly large, which they run their swarm around in, the number one cause of a zone threatening blowup is someone else running their pull or quad thru it, especially a pull. There is a very high aggro factor to a charm whopping on another mob, someone using a snare or other low damage/aggro pull will run by a charm battling mobs and their pull will stop and start whumping the bard or the charm and the puller starts oocing Ks, Ks! I have had my group of for in ME added to by at least three other pullers and what was a managble kite becomes a death run of 10 to 20 mobs to the zone. Only those watching from a distance find this amusing.<br>
<br>
Pick a forum, any class, and you can go there and find your class and most the others, bashed, because someone is envious of what u do well, or they have been abused either deservably or not by someone of that class.  I have people pull from my swarms all the time, usually it is 'to help' or an accident. Who cares? If theres plenty of mobs, just get sumore, if not, find another zone or live with it.<br>
<br>
Every forum gripes about being nerfed. Every one of them. And complains any upgrades were useless, and x class, who was overpowered before, is now even stronger. <br>
<br>
I thought a single group of wizards taking down a dragon was neat. Probably would have been nerfed at some point, but a few bad apples monopolizing the scales on some servers, and poof, there's an uproar about money grubbing wizards holding everyone else hostage.  <br>
<br>
Are there bad bards who abuse their gifts, oh yeah! Ditto for every other class.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deamereq>DeamerEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(11/1/02 2:18:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=87>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Swarm Kiting</span><hr size=1> Well, I happen to know for a fact there is a macro program used for swarm kiting.  There is no pet involved and you only need to watch your screen to make sure the program didn't crash on you(which it does quite often).  <br>
